In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. Roughly
chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%oz}
to taste.

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a large pan
over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring, until browned all over,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Shredded Carrots{4%oz}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tbsp}, and @Sesame Dressing{1.5%oz}.
Cook until carrots are softened, chicken is cooked through, and sauce has thickened,
~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest and @Butter{1%tbsp}. Season with
salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken mixture and any remaining
sauce from pan. Drizzle with chili mayo. Sprinkle with @Crispy Fried Onions{1}
and cilantro. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.